reviews:
My wife and I just spent three nights at the Terrass" Hotel. Perfect location to explore Montmartre Paris. You can walk to the center of the action. Restaurants are plentiful and a grocery store is right next door.
The front desk staff are excellent. I was actually surprised everyone spoke perfect English, which was a relief. My French needs a lot of work.
We stayed in room 116. Decent size bedroom and a huge bathroom.
Our only complaint was the air conditioning. It's still rather cool in May at night and in the early morning, but daytime temperatures got into the mid to high 80s and the room became stuffy and hot. The A/C was very weak. The French aren't known for using A/C, but with global warming kicking into high gear, that A/C needs to improve.

We have stayed in many hotels around the world as I travel for business. Terrass is right up there.
It’s extremely clean, very spacious rooms and well fitted out. Easy to get too from both local train stations and the Eurostar. The hotel has some amazing views of Paris from its roof top terrace restaurant and bar.

The morning breakfasts are also very good again having stayed in many hotels this was great and with an awesome view.

Everyone in the hotel is very helpful, particularly Hanae, who gave us her time and a map and showed us some of the best places to go in the city and how to get there. She even gave us specific instruction on how to use the trains lines and where to capture some unique glimpses of Paris that only the locals know about. Thank you Hanae you made your first trip to Paris a time to remember for life.

We would recommend this hotel to everyone visiting Paris.

Thank you Hotel Terrass it’s been amazing.

This is a magical place. The view from the terrace is unique. You can see whole Paris on your palm. The servise and cleannes is perfect. The restorant is on the level of the best Michelin places. We enoy and looking forward to visit more! Highly recommended!

What’s an absolute excellent hotel, with absolute excellent staff, including Sarha and Paulettee on reception, housekeeping very accommodating, an absolute diamond close to bus stops and the Metro, and if you need any help at all girls on the front desk or 2nd to none!
I wholeheartedly recommend this lovely hotel

We were lucky enough to recently stay at the Terrass Hotel in Paris. The location was superb and the staff were excellent.

We would definitely stay here again.

We would be more than happy to recommend the Hotel to friends and family.

Stayed here for 2 nights before heading to the Loire Region and the castles. Excellent hotel. Very friendly and helpful staff. Breakfast area on top floor has terrific views of Paris. Rooftop bar is a nice spot for a drink after walking Paris streets. Nice restaurants in the area. Short walk to Montmartre and Sacre Coeur. 7 minute walk to the Moulin Rouge. Safe walk back after the 11 pm show.

Stayed here before our "girl's birthday trip " to Morocco. It was wonderful! Great Staff , amazing location with beautiful Paris views. I enjoyed it so much I went back immediately after our trip for 3 days more.
The amenities including availability to hire onsight driver to airport. The rooms are excellent , comfortable and well appointed Recommended to all my friends and family and I will BE BACK.

The room looked into another wing of the hotel, little light, no view.
The bathroom is built into the room with a metal wall.
Shower had continuously changing water temperature.
Noisy.
Spa not available.
Storage for clothing in the room was minimal. Hanging rack, one or two shelves. No closet.

Very helpful and friendly receptionists. Excellent hotel, very well located in Montmartre.
The hotel lounge area was stylishly decorated as was our room. Very comfortable and relaxing. A short walk to many bars and restaurants. Close to 2 metro stations and a bus stop. The Moulin Rouge, Sacre Coeur and many other 'must see ' sites are all within walking distance.

We knew of the rooftop bar from a previous stay. We remembered their special Raclette dinner and made an advance reservation.
So we thought, we reserved the wrong place.
Thankfully they figured a creative solution! They served us in the ski hut they have tucked in back! We did not have a view but had a great warm place to enjoy our much anticipated event.
We are very happy with this experience and the extra effort on the part of the bar and restaurant staff.

hotel very well located although difficult to reach depending on whether you know the area or not. Nothing to complain about in terms of the cleanliness of the rooms or even the decor of the hotel which remains splendid for a Parisian hotel. I would have appreciated more sympathy from the front desk staff. Some of them leave something to be desired, they don't even take the time to give you a smile and when we walk to them, they answer us as if it was bothering them! On the other hand, some of them take the time to sympathize and discuss with us, you can see that they love their job! Thank you to the kind Hanae who takes the time to suggest great places to visit, and thank you to the beautiful Sarah for her daily smile and the time she takes to chat with each of us as soon as she gets there. I would definitely come back for the friendliness of some of the staff and for the wonderful pictures I was able to take, I still have so much to see of the city! Hanae, Sarah I count on you to make me discover more!

A big thank you to the people in charge of the Terrass Hotel who have made it a magical establishment. A special mention to the young brunette (Sara?) and the Red-beard who took care of our well-being day after day. Another big thank you to the same young lady who shared with us her passion for architecture and who recommended us some breathtaking sceneries to visit in Paris and who recommended us some restaurants : we couldn't stop eating! The cleanliness and hospitality of this hotel made us feel at home, thank you for everything, we will be back as soon as possible!

Friendly, helpful staff, superb roof terrace bar with fantastic views, great location to explore both locally and easy access to central Paris. All round comfortable well kept hotel, highly recommended

My daughter and I have just spent 4 nights in The Terrass hotel in the artist studio. The entire experience was faultless from the delicious breakfasts to the wonderful room to incredible views, all in the heart of the beautiful Montmarte area. Margaux on reception went over and beyond each and every day with her advice on amazing places to visit. She was incredibly helpful and so generous with her time. I would highly recommend this hotel. If we are ever back in Paris this will definitely be our go to hotel!!

This was our first time to Paris and we couldn’t of wished for a nicer Hotel. The staff were very friendly and helpful, nothing was too much trouble for them.
It was my Husbands Birthday and a lovely complimentary bottle of wine was placed in our room on our arrival.
Only a short walk to Sacre Coeur, Moulin Rouge and the Metro.
We would definitely stay here again and would recommend to any friends and family that intend to Travel to Paris.

My husband planned a trip for my Christmas gift! Booked with our travel agent. Made no requests except a superior room. We arrived late in evening. Check in no problem. Our room on 3rd floor looked into the courtyard. It was fine though. Lovely comfortable room. Good storage. Tea and coffee tray. Linens and towels were lovely. Robes and slippers and loccitane products were great. Spacious bathroom and shower. Great lighting in the room. Never had to adjust heating once. Felt secure and very quiet. Housekeeping excellent. Second to none. Reception team always greeted us and really helpful with any direction we needed. Breakfast is something else. The views are amazing. Good food with all you could want. Never too busy. Lovely man with glasses in charge. Quiet and efficient. Sorry didn’t ask his name. Created a calm peaceful atmosphere.
Visited the roof top bar which was warm and comfortable even in February.
Stayed 4 nights. Wished I could say I will go back but probably won’t be that lucky!
The area is perfect. Monmartre is the only area to stay in. Well done Terrasse hotel. Just how a hotel stay should be. X

Our stay at the Terrass Hotel was top quality. The bedroom was very modern and spacious with a comfortable bed. We had a double room with a stunning view of the Eiffel Tower.
The bathroom was super luxurious with a large shower and large stand alone bath. We even had a view of the Eiffel Tower from the bath!

We ate in the rooftop restaurant one of the nights which was one of our trip highlights. The food and service were great and we enjoyed one of the nicest bottles of white wine!

The location was central and perfect for walking around the city, with lots of nice restaurants in the area.

Overall we thoroughly enjoyed staying here and would return again on our next trip to Paris.

The location, the Hotel & the staff...everything was perfect!
Perfect located!
Bar & Restaurant with stunning views!
The staff was nice & kind!
Paul from reception was sooo nice!
Top place!
Here’s a view from our breakfast table!

The Terras Hotel has an exquisite atmosphere and beautiful decor! I was very kindly treated on my birthday by them. They left me a free bottle of wine and notes as well as little trinkets in my room. In addition to being located in a beautiful area of Paris, the hotel is near tourist sites, restaurants, bars, and stores that are all within walking distance. In every corner of the hotel, there is a perfect background for a picture. The rooftop bar and restaurant were beautifully decorated inside and were so inviting for breakfast, lunch, dinner, and drinks. In one case, we were unable to gain entry to the hotel after returning from a late-night dinner. The hotel, however, handled the situation very well and offered compensation for our troubles. In addition, if you are booking a room for more than two people, make sure you call the hotel about the extra bed since it is not covered by Expedia. It was a great place to stay in Paris!

So impressed by the hotel , clean , central and stylish
But the best thing about it is the helpful staff in particular Sara at the front desk
She was amazing in helping us all the time and she have a great attitude
I will stay in this hotel again. Because guest services are avital in my travel

What a wonderful hotel! The staff, the restaurant, the view of the Eiffel Tower from our room were all just unbelievable. We felt so comfortable and taken care of by reception. We look forward to returning as soon as we can!

Fabulous hotel, the best stay we have had in Paris. Really professional, helpful staff on the front desk. We had breakfast in the rooftop restaurant which was excellent every morning, with views over paris that were nothing less than spectacular .we tried the outdoor rooftop var, which was great, and even in December, really popular. Very comfortable room, and amazing barhroom. The terrass Hotel is located in monmartre village, a really bustling area , just down from sacre coeur, great for having a drink at a local bar, or a fabulous meal . We are already planning our next stay at the terrass Hotel.

Good hotel, well located. The rooms are pretty cool in terms of how they’re decorated with a good standard of toiletries and linens.

Sadly the first room we had smelled badly of sewage so we had to move rooms - hence the mark down.

The staff were generally very friendly and helpful and the rooftop bar is worth a drink even though somewhat overpriced.

The classic rooms are very small (fairly standard for Paris) but the superior rooms are better. Be mindful as rooms over the road can get noisy with the traffic.

Walking distance from montmartre and loads of bars and restaurants nearby.

This hotel really does have everything - comfortable, well stocked rooms, fab decor, great food and drink and of course, the stunning views. I loved the proximity to Montmartre too. Staff were friendly and attentive and nothing was too much trouble. Will definitely be returning. A great find!

My husband and I visited for the first time for a few days. The hotel is in a great location in the Montemarte neighborhood of Paris. The staff was wonderful! Very helpful with suggestions and assistance. This hotel is about a 25 minute cab ride to the Eiffel Tower and attractions. Several cafes, restaurants, markets, bakeries and Sacre Coeur Cathedral within walking distances. Will definitely be back! The Bacotes.

My room was under the rooftop bar and next to the maids quarters so it was a double whammy of noise. Loud cleanup until 2:30am and then maids arriving at 6am each morning. I’m exhausted to say the least. The restaurant was so loud my entire room would shake, the glasses fell off of the cart where the fridge was. Also the terrace is shared so the other room could walk to see into my room. There are also no safety locks on the doors so any staff could come in at anytime. For a solo traveler I didn’t feel as safe as I should have for the price. If I had been in a different room I might have had a better experience.

Location is good, nice terrace with good view. Rooftop bar is adorable with nice staff but pricey. Wonderful restaurants within a few minutes walking distance and a intermarche down the street.

I really wanted to like this place because I did a ton of research for staying in Montmarte and the social media was great. Turns out it was greets marketing. Overall I think the hotel is not worth the cost. I would not stay here again.

We were here for 3 nights. Hotel’s location is great. Lobby is very nice and has cool design. Rooms are very comfortable. Terrace of the hotel is so unique. We felt like we spent very special time. The best thing about this hotel is the team. Zeliha is great person who is in charge at Terrass Cafe. She is so kind and very helpful about every detail. Johan at reception he is also gave us many good advice. Totally nice experience! Bon voyage…

I have never been to a hotel with such great service. Even when we weren't the easiest customers, we were always handled with the utmost grace. The breakfast was fantastic. The rooms are nice. I highly recommend.

I loved my luxurious five-night stay in a beautifully designed and decorated "artist studio" apartment, with a fabulous view of Paris, featuring the Eiffel Tower, from the balcony! The location in vibrant Montmartre was perfect, with many great eateries and stores virtually on the doorstep, along with proximity to two metro stations. The historic cemetery across the road was an interesting place to visit, and I walked up to the gorgeous Sacré-Cœur one evening. When I arrived at the hotel prior to check-in, a staff member came out to meet me right away, and I was invited to enjoy a complimentary coffee in the attractive foyer area while I waited. The staff were helpful throughout. The moving pictures in the lift were very cool! The rooftop bar (also serving finger food) has great views and a pleasant ambiance. Enhancements in my apartment which I particularly appreciated were the Marshall amplifier, the long and deep bath with a new bath cube provided every day, and the lovely colourful dried flower arrangement. Oh, and the excellent coffee machine! And the "welcome" gift! The room service meals I ordered were very good too. Email communications before my stay were informative. Overall, one of the best hotel experiences I've ever had - it was wonderful, merci beaucoup!

Air conditioning is turned off and rooms are very hot.
The windows don’t have screens and must be open, otherwise the temperature is 30 degrees Celsius which makes for sleepless nights.
I am hearing other guests complaining about the same issues as I write this review

Just got back from an amazing weekend in Paris with 4 friends. The foundation to us having such a great time was this hotel. Such a brilliant place to find and it isn’t often you arrive at a hotel for it to look better in real life than it does in the photos. I was really nervous as I know many hotels in Paris (as with other cities) can be really tiny. We were an odd number, so booked 2 rooms, one made up with 3 beds. I could not have been happier when we arrived and all rooms were set up perfectly and the 3rd bed looked just like a double and was super comfy (despite being a sofa bed). The bathrooms were perfect and stocked with L’Occitane products. Our rooms were super clean and quiet, very comfy beds, the whole hotel beautifully decorated and the roof terrace just spectacular. We booked rooms with an Eiffel Tower view which was wonderful. Everyone super friendly and helpful. Perfect location in Montmartre close to a Metro stop. I can’t recommend it enough if you are looking for a place to stay for the weekend. I will be back with my husband!

The room is formidable even without a view aristic room delivers . Bathroom extremely large and well equipped. Breakfast is extra 25€ but worth it Not at least for the view And very close to attractions such as Sacré-Cœur ,Molain rouge and Le mur de Je t’aime

Stayed here for three nights in September. We had a lovely room, which was very quiet, number 111. Very comfortable bed. Staff are very helpful. Love to the location in Monmartre.
The Terrace is exceptional, great spot for a drink before dinner. A little pricey, but you pay for the view! We had breakfast one morning in the restaurant. Excellent selection and very helpful staff. Would highly recommend this hotel for a trip to Paris.

We have stayed at this hotel every year since they reopened in 2015, bringing friends and referring to all. This visit was sub-par. The quality of the staff and the rooms have declined since 2019. Rooms were not throughly cleaned with remnants from previous guests. Hotel staff used to be superior always going above and beyond for guests, not it is average at best.

Excellent staff
knowledge of transport system to visit all tourist sites very good
Hotel location excellent nearby restaurant and bars
Rooms cleaned daily
Roof top bar best view of eiffal
Tower
Well done to the staff and management

My wife and I enjoyed our week-long stay. The lobby, elevators, and room were spotless and comfortable. I can't say enough about the staff, from front desk to housekeeping -- always smiling and willing to assist. The location was perfect -- close to everything (restaurants, cafes, shopping centers, transit). You must also check out the rooftop at least once and soak in the views, including the Eiffel Tower at night.

Would stay here again.

Great boutique hotel.
Good guest service. Adele and Melvin at the front are phenomenal at what they do. Clean and walkable to many restaurants and bars. Had a nice coffee station downstairs and good breakfast buffet in the morning.
They have a famous rooftop bar that is very popular and always has a wait. Great view of the Eiffel Tower from the roof.
Good service there as well.

Had a four night stay here, great hotel in a lively location with plenty of bars and restaurants in walking distance also two metro stops within a ten minute walk. The rooms were spotless and we were lucky enough to get one with views of the effiel tower, there is a roof top bar and restaurant on the seventh floor with panoramic views over Paris, we pre booked the set meal for two on one night and it was excellent value could not fault the service or food will definitely use this hotel again

Really good hotel. Great staff. Great location with lovely restaurants and shops around. Best of the three we tried, beautiful room, fantastic staff. Great coffee. I would definitely recommend this hotel.

Overall we had a very positive experience staying at this hotel. The location in Montmarte is tremendous - so close and walkable to many restaurants and sites.

I will start with a few minor negatives. We were a family of 5 (2 adults and 3 children ages 8, 10, 12). I had painstakingly searched for Paris hotels that offered connecting rooms. I communicated with Terrass Hotel staff often and confirmed several times that we had connecting rooms. We booked an Artist Studio Suite and a Classic Standard Room and were assured these rooms would provide connecting rooms. However, upon arrival we found that “connecting”apparently translated to two separate rooms at the end of a hallway with entry doors facing each other. While this was not ideal for us, we made it work and let our 3 kids sleep in the suite while my wife and I slept across the hall in the Classic room. I was a little anxious about this set-up at first, but it worked out.

This little mix-up was the only flaw of our entire stay. Yes - we would have preferred beds that were not as firm as these. And yes we would have preferred the air conditioning was a little more powerful. And perhaps it would have been nice to have a little more space in the rooms (although, for normal Paris hotel standards, these rooms were above average space-wise).

Now the positives. Location! Location! Location! The hotel is a short walk to a number of metro stops / lines making it very convenient to explore Paris. The hotel is not near the main sites, but the metro allowed for efficient transport. We bought a 5-day metro pass and got more than our money’s worth. Montmarte is a great place to stay in Paris. So many cafes and restaurants within a short walk. The alleys and small streets of Montmarte are quintessentially Paris! The Sacre Couer is also walkable from the hotel.

This is a very chic and trendy boutique hotel. Fabulous decor, super trendy bar / lounge on the rooftop terrace with amazing views of the Eifel Tower. Very friendly staff that helped us with any questions. The hotel arranged for transportation from the airport on arrival and also to the train station upon departure, both of which were safe, reliable, and timely. The breakfast buffet was quite enjoyable although we only had it once since it was expensive for children (kids pay full price - 25 euros - even if they only eat a croissant and have some water).

There were not a lot of children at the hotel and the hotel is not overly geared to children, but they were more than accommodating of ours. If your children are somewhat rambunctious, this may not be the best place given how quiet the hotel is.

Speaking of quiet, our rooms were on the third floor and we did not hear a sound from the street below or the lounge above on any of our 5-nights. We were all able to rest quietly.

Otherwise, the rooms were comfortable. The beds were firm for our taste, but manageable. Great showers! Plenty of hot water with good water pressure. The Classic room bathroom is tight but OK for 2 people. The Artist Studio Suite bathroom was spacious and beautiful.

I would definitely stay here again when visiting Paris.

We absolutely loved the Terrass” Hotel! Perfect location in our favourite area of Paris, Montmartre! Fabulous front desk crew (Alène and Léa I believe were their names) and the restaurant and bar crew were great! We highly recommend and will definitely be returning!

The stay in Terrass was a mixed feeling. I stayed for 5 days 4 nights. In general, the hotel should have better service, better maintenance, and better quality management for a €200/night rate. The price doesn’t match the service. I am a frequent traveler that stays ranging from boutique to luxury hotel, therefore I do have valid comparisons. Here’s my honest opinion:

Cons:
1. 2 days of not functioning hot water (from the shower and basin). We called at least 5 times because the Staff said someone will call us back in 10 minutes but no one came back to us for at least 2 hours. At the end, the Staff tried to give us a good gesture by giving me free breakfast but when I checked out, they charged us. I had to complain for them to fix it.
2. Breakfast selection was very minimal and not tasty for a €25 price.
3. TV is not working properly. Sound keeps cracking.
4. There are some stains on the wall, curtain, and floor.

Neutral:
1. Some of the staffs are unfriendly and not attentive but some are helpful.

Pros:
1. The amenities in the room are quite complete for the essential stuffs.
2. The location is quite strategic. Just at the edge of Montmatre. You can find Lime, Tier, Dott just in front of the hotel. Plenty of restaurants nearby.
3. Bed was comfortable.

In conclusion, the rate is overpriced for the quality that they offer.

Really nice hotel in a wonderful spot in charming Montmartre. Our room was very spacious and comfortable, staff very helpful and friendly, and we enjoyed a lovely meal in the rooftop restaurant. There’s also a Nuxe spa which I would love to try next time! My only criticism was the hairdryer - didn’t really work and was too hot even on the lowest setting. A small thing in what was otherwise a fabulous stay.

My husband, daughter and I stayed at the Terrass at the end of June into July 2022 for about 4 nights. The room was phenomenal, spacious and well appointed for the three of us. The bathroom boasted a tub and a shower which had excellent water pressure and loads of hot water. I think we had 10 ply toilet paper :) . There was complimentary sparkling and still drinking water at reception in addition to coffee. The room also had a small coffee maker and a mini fridge. Staff were very friendly and always willing to give me directions and recommend restaurants. Off course mere footsteps outside the hotel , you will find several lovely restaurants as well as groceries, boulangeries etc. The hotel is also about a 15 - 20 minute walk to Sacre Coeur. I would highly recommend this hotel, it was perfection. Also from the roof top restaurant, you get a lovely view from Paris and the Eiffel Tower was visible at night from our balcony.

Had another wonderful stay at this lovely hotel. I have been staying at this Montmartre hotel for over 10 years and it’s only gotten better.
Small enough so that you do not feel lost in the crowd. No long lines to check in here…(unlike the Hyatt Étoile we stayed at recently). Super friendly, polite (multilingual) front desk staff and a lovely bellman who greeted me warmly each time I walked through the reception area. Hotel is in an Excellent location, situated in an neighborhood with many good restaurants (try Le Piano Perché), prize-winning boulangeries, cheese emporiums, chocolate, gelato and crepe shops. It’s a foodie paradise.
Cannot recommend it enough. Do suggest you book early on in March or April if you plan on visiting over the summer. (Rates are very reasonable)

The reception staff was fabulous from check in, to great restaurant recommendations and booking car service to return to the airport. Awesome roof top bar, with incredible views of the Eiffel Tower. Rooms are nice and clean (not elegant) with great views and windows that open wide.

Had an amazing experience at Terrass Hotel. Would recommend it to anyone and everyone. Quality and customer service were impeccable. The location cannot be beat! And the rooftop bar is unparalleled with an amazing view of the city. We had a wonderful time.

We loved our stay at the Terrass. It’s charming, has comfortable rooms, and the staff is off the charts helpful. We had a hiccup where our room was the only one in the whole hotel to lose power; Anna worked with the electrical crew to troubleshoot right away, and when it couldn’t be solved quickly she moved us to an even nicer room. The rooftop bar is a highlight, with its view of the Eiffel tower and great food and drinks. Another highlight is the free Nespresso machine and seltzer water in the lobby. My boyfriend was going crazy over both. We will definitely return!

Me, my mother and my sister was staying at the hotell on our girlstrip. The place was perfect. The room was big and clean, the restaurant and bar on the topfloor had an amazing view over Paris. I would like to come back!

I was looking for somewhere special for breakfast and a Google search brought up here. The breakfast room on the 7th floor had beautiful sweeping views across the Paris skyline. Breakfast was a choice of buffet or a la Carte. When we looked at the limited enough buffet option we decided to order off the menu. The restaurant was pretty full when we arrived so it was hard to get the staffs attention so we helped ourselves to tea & coffee. Our egg dishes were lovely and with the accompanying view it made for a nice experience.

We spent 2 nights in Paris as part of a 2 week vacation in France. We arrived early morning and were pleasantly surprised that we could enjoy a wonderful breakfast in their rooftop restaurant and our room was available after we finished. We were able to freshen up and rest a bit before heading out to explore the city and try to get on Paris time. The hotel is close to Sacre Cour, but did not feel overly touristy. Our room was beautiful, very comfortable and had a great view of the city including the Eifel Tower. The staff at the front desk and the restaurant were incredibly helpful and kind.

A simply outstanding service from booking to arriving. The warm efficient welcome from the staff at the front desk and the excellent accommodation. Make sure you try and get room a room with a view higher up - stunning views and access to the roof terrace which is something people come and queue for at the busy times. Such a great find as you have all of the restaurants and bars of Montmartre on your doorstep and access to the Metro. Simply excellent holiday - thank you

Great location at the base of Montmartre. Lovely neighbourhood full of good bistros and restaurants.
The hotel has been recently renovated and has a very classy feel to it without being at all pretentious.
The rooms are on the small side but with comfortable beds and good sound proofing to the street. West facing rooms, particularly higher up have spectacular views, with south facing rooms on the higher floors having a view over the Eifel tower.
Beds are comfortable, shower OK.
The eponymous roof terrace is the jewel in this hotels crown with priority access to residents and great views.
Service is friendly and the food is good.

We stayed for a romantic weekend at this beautiful hotel, and we had the best time. Staff was very friendly and accommodating, the room was comfortable and nice.

The location is truly one of the best in Paris: so close to the great dining and shopping areas of Abessess and Montmartre.

Also, the rooftop bar where breakfast is served has a gorgeous view of Paris with the Eiffel tower! Could not stop admiring the view. Also, the breakfast buffet itself is probably one of the best hotel breakfast experiences I've ever had. Lots of choises of bread, brioche, waffles, pancakes, yoghurt, juices, sweets and treats, cheeses, et cetera, et cetera.

we have visited Paris this february, first time in covid 19 period! It was some new experience but the Terrass was in excellent condition! The staff was kind and always on service! The top experiance is on the top of the hotel: restaurant and the bar and the view. You have to see it, in one word, incredible 👍
Location of the hotel is excellent, it is in the heart of Monmartre but conected very well by the buses and metro lines with other hystorical and turist's places. I really think that in some period of our life, we deserve to have this incredible experience, especialy after this two passive years 😉

Radha S.

Every person working here was so friendly and accommodating! They gave us great recommendations on local restaurants and were always available to answer any questions we might have. The room was very comfortable and clean. Would definitely stay here again on any future trips to Paris!

Wonderful hotel at the edge of Montmatre with most amazing view for breakfast and stunning views from the terrace. You can-quick access the rooftop bar as hotel guest and skip the queues in summer, which is very nice. Been coming here for several occasions since 2015.

Rooms are modern and stylish, but the best part is that the windows are sound proofed and no street noise to be heard during the night.

We send all our family and friends to this hotel when they are in town!

Can highly recommend.

Absolutely amazing hotel, nice room, super service, breakfast with a view, spa. Everything you can wish for.

The area of the hotel is also pleasant.

P.S next time we would like your cleaning staff to be more precise and clean our room. For 3 days we didn’t got any cleaning.

I have stayed at this hotel a few times and the standards are always very high. The staff are charming, the location is great and the bed are so comfortable it is like sleeping on a cloud. It is a great hotel to explore Paris from. Most things are about 30 mins away by metro as well as everything to do just on the doorstep.

Had a wonderful stay at the Terrass Hotel. It is located in a funky Paris neighborhood not too far from the Moulin Rouge. The hotel features a restaurant (great breakfast buffet) on the top level with a breathtaking panoramic view of Paris. But the best part is the front desk staff. Special shoutout to Hanae, we will always be grateful for all your assistance!

Following previous visits to Paris we decided to explore Montmartre area for a change. The Terrass Hotel is perfectly located for enjoying this magical part of the city. Our room was very clean, spacious and light with 2 windows with great views across the city. The main attraction for us were the roof top bar and restaurant on the 7th floor. Wrap up warmly if visiting the bar in Winter months. The staff are friendly and breakfast was well organised with plenty of fresh food choices. We both felt we were really able to enjoy a whole new Paris… thoroughly recommend!

Close to many restaurants and bars Nice clean rooms A little difficult to adjust room temperature Beds a little too short and narrow Breakfast is recommended and to pay in advance An excellent view over Paris and La tour eiffel if you book ”Studio d’Artiste Eiffel” I would stay there again for sure

Perfectly located in Monmartre, a great walking area, tons of cafes, etc, and if you get an Eiffel room, you go to sleep watching the flickering (on the hour). Breakfast is great (lots of salmon, eggs to order), good coffee, extremely pleasant staff. Front desk is efficient, friendly and great communications. Room is very comfortable. Get one with a balcony!

Nice hotel! Wonderful views. Nice location. You can enjoy the walk in the Montmartre neighbourhood.

Nice service, very friendly and helpful.

Great breakfast, fresh food, wonderful breads and gourmet cheeses, you can order eggs, plus you can enjoy amazing views to the city and the Eiffel Tower while having your breakfast.

Room are a bit small but comfortable and super clean.
The sky bar is great. You can enjoy the lights of the city and the Eiffel Tower.

Oh, where to begin….

The hotel was informed that we would arrive early and even offered us an early check in option; however, not only was the room not ready early, we were not assigned until nearly 17:00 and almost late to our evening ballet at the Opera House. Oh, and there is that other detail, the first room we were assigned had a couple already in it wondering why we were walking in on them. Awkward.

We finally got a room. It was okay, but nothing special. It was a spacious room by Paris hotel standards, but that is it. We didn’t have a city view or anything.

The area of the hotel is okay, but be prepared for waking up and down hills, an inconvenient metro stop location (with a lot of stairs), and a hit and miss restaurant/cafe location. The best cafes were several blocks away.

This is an okay hotel in the Montmartre, but we will not stay here again next time we come to Paris.

Tried to check in early. They said sorry your room is not ready. Okay. We walked around til 330 or so. They said the room is still not ready. I had prepaid for an Executive Suite! We want to visit the Paris Opera and came back...it finally was ready. The young lady offered to give us free continental breakfast...I said I had already paid for it.
The next morning I told another desk guy that the shower was clogged. He said he would take care of it. When we got back it wasn't taken care of because there was only 1 key! He said he would buy us a couple drinks at the rooftop bar. We had 2 beers and 2 wines...he picked up 1 of each.
He brought me the key (the only key) and apologized. We went to the room. The clog was fixed but no maid had been in.
So I was on the bed waiting at 530 while the maid vacuumed and cleaned up.
He apologized the next day and said he spoke to the manager and said there would be a discount. I haven't seen it.
I kinda thought folks in the hotel business are supposed to make things nice and comfortable for you.
Did the guy who stayed late get a free day?
They made sure to take out the money for the bottle of beer from the minibar that I drank to soothe my ire.
The management sent me a form letter and asked about my stay. I replied with the same info I'm posting here. He never wrote back.
The front desk people did the best they could I suppose but it just seems like a crappy way to treat a customer.

My wife and I stayed for 5 days in July at Terrass. Montmartre is an amazing neighborhood, especially for those who like a more village-y vibe and this hotel is superbly located just down the street from great cafes, wine bars, and restaurants. The room was well decorated, very comfortable, and had a nice balcony. I wish the hotel had free coffee in the room (we found this many other places), but for the price we paid, this is 100% worth it. Walk over to La Bossue or Boris Lume for coffee, grab croissants at Alexine, and get wine at Gisou.

A couple notes: this is not in the 6eme, so expect a Metro ride to get to major attractions (except Sacre Coeur), but if you're in Paris for long enough and willing to live like a local, this place is super worth it.

We were some of the first Americans back to visit Paris after the COVID restrictions and could not have received a warmer welcome by the staff at the Terrass Hotel. They were all very nice, accommodating and friendly. The room we had was beautiful, large and came with an incredible bathroom complete with soaking tub, shower, double sinks, basically a spa. The hotel was very clean. Located in a very central area of Montmartre, we easily walked to restaurants and our favorite attractions. Their rooftop deck is very popular and as a guest you get preferred access. Overall a wonderful stay. We will definitely be back!

The hotel is super nice, comfort, well located, nice amenities, average/good breakfast (nothing special), amazing bed, great tour eiffel view.. but the staff really ruined my stay.. they were so moody, rude and not kind AT ALL. Anyway, I would recommend the place because of the rest.

First time in this hotel - great ambiance - fantastic service - great location - roof top restaurant and bar is a great experience - could feel the boutique mindset even though the hotel is relatively big. Lovely experience all in all

Absolutely loved our stay. The hotel staff was friendly and helpful, room had plenty of space and the balcony had an amazing view of the city. Also loved our dinner at the restaurant and the view form the bar is unbeatable. Would definitely stay again in the future.

What an Amazing stay! The hotel is very well located near Montmartre and Pigalle with a spectacular view on the Eiffel Tower. The hotel is very elegant and the room are modern and stylish. A big thank you to the team who has been looking after us.

Beautiful hotel, the furnishing and decoration are amazing and the view from the restaurant on the rooftop is just breathtaking. Comfy bed and nice effective staff, anything you need is made in the five minutes following your request. The location is perfect if you want to visit Montmartre but a bit out of the city center, yet again in Paris nothing is very far with the Metro. I took one point off for 2 reasons: the beverages at the bar are ridiculously expensive (17€ a cocktail and 6€ for a syrup drop in filtered tap water), ok we’re in Paris but still! Also the pillows might need to be changed, ours were flat and hard. But still a very nice hotel and a wonderful stay.

We drew back the curtains flung wide the French Windows and there before us was this amazing view of Paris in the warm sunshine. The Eiffel tower shimmering in the distance and even more impressive at night with the twinkling lights and laser beam.
It is not the idealised view that one would purchase from a 'boite' by the Seine. There are some ugly modern buildings in sight and the funerary chapels of the Montmartre cemetery are an acquired taste but the Tower and the sublime golden dome of Les Invalides crowns this tremendous sight.
Why am I spending so much time on this description? The room itself 'Studio d'Artiste Eiffel', its furniture and fittings are just fine but they could be in any 4 star hotel any where.This view from the French windows raised our stay into a totally superior category.
I noticed that there were some complaints about street noise. We did not find it a problem. Perhaps the glazing is better but as Stakhanovites of of the tourist visit we were usually under way by 8.00 am.
Alas for the buffet breakfast, although the staff did their best with the pre-ordering system. We were disappointed with tiny sausages which accompanied the omelettes but this is really a clash of cultures. As Northerners one of our Cumberland sausage would need at least 6 of their Parisian cousins.
Two tips:- The view from the front pavement of the Sacre Coeur is magnificent and faces more to the East. It is a steep climb and you can eat well in the place du Tertre.
Paris is very walkable. Although the Eiffel Tower seems far away it is a fine trip to go Clichy, Monceau , CDG Etoile, Pont D'Alma and mostly downhill.

The hotel was very clean. The rooms were small but that was to be expected. The location was not a great as I thought it like be considering all the reviews saying it was great. I felt the staff was very dismissive. Particularly on the parking, you are suppose to get a discounted price in the parking garage when you stay there, which they advertise and before we paid my husband asked them how he would get it and they told him to just go pay. But that was not the case instead of 48 euro we paid 78 euro. They told me that there was not much they could do since we already paid them. When they told us to do it. They said they would contact their manager to see if there was anything they could do. I have yet to hear back. Many other concerns I had brought up were dismissed I understand there is a language barrier but I do not feel they should’ve been so dismissive.

Clean, staff is friendly, cool retro feel. Definitely more posh than most traditional European hotels. Would highly recommend for anyone staying in Montmartre. Whenever we had an issue (we had one with the C), they fixed it right away. Beautiful rooftop bar overlooking the Eiffel Tower.

I hadn't been to Paris in many years and my french was wonky, to say the least, so I wanted to stay somewhere that would serve as a home base as I explored the city. I could not have gotten any luckier than choosing the Terrass. Not only was my room clean and beautiful, but I had the luck of snagging an incredible view of the city. And the staff—from the concierge to the restaurants to the maids—were all polite and happy to help with any issues. It was the perfect place to come back to after long days.

And, because it's located in the gorgeous Montmartre neighborhood, you're close to Sacre Coeur as well as a host of beautiful winding streets, boulangeries, brasseries, and shops, so if you decide you're too tired to leave the area, everything nearby is a treat. That's including the amazing terrace bar in the hotel that serves as a destination for Parisians and international visitors alike. Each time I went I met someone new and interesting. Overall, a wonderful stay and I will definitely be back!

Loved the view, our room was fantastic, very was wonderul.
The roof top bar with a night view of the Eiffel Tower
As a travel consultant I would sell this with out hesitatation.
Loved that we could walk right up the street in either direction to restraunats
shops etc, bus and other transpertation very close by

We had a one night layover in Paris and chose this hotel due to its close proximity to Moulin Rouge show. Got the smallest room with a view of the Eiffel tower. The room was very clean, the view was great, staff was very friendly and helpful, restaurant vibe was cool, the terrace bar was even cooler. They arranged our airport transfers and everything was smooth. Just great service all around. Restaurant was a little pricey, but very cool to eat dinner with a panoramic view of the Eiffel tower. Also the lift doesn't go all the way to the 8th floor, you have to walk up the stairs so if you have special needs please let them know ahead of time. Would have loved a couple of more nights at this lovely hotel.

I’ve just returned from a 4 night stay at the Terrass with my partner & I don’t have a single bad thing to say about this hotel. From check-in until check-out, we received nothing less than excellent service from every member of staff. The hotel itself is modern yet comfortable & it’s location makes it an ideal basis for exploring Montmartre. It’s also incredibly close to Abbesses Metro station, if you’re looking to go further afield.

We stayed in an Executive Eiffel room, which I would go for again on our next visit (and there will definitely be a next visit)! The room was clean, trendy & spacious. And having the Eiffel Tower sparkling at you from across the city was the perfect end to each night.

We ate at the hotel restaurant on our 1st night, and I would recommend this to anyone, even if you’re not staying at the hotel. The food, the service, the atmosphere - everything was exceptional! A truly special experience for our 1st night.

Breakfast is a more relaxed experience but no less excellent. For someone who normally skips breakfast, I went back for seconds every day!

Overall, I’d recommend this hotel to anyone planning a few days in Paris.

Charming lobby & comfy rooms w/ a cool vibe. Convenient location to lots of bakeries,restaurants,shops, oh la la! The staff is excellent & Vincent at the front desk is outstanding. We loved the view & food at the buffet breakfast!

I had been at the Terrass last year and I liked it very much, so I decided to stay again this year for three nights and I took a “better” (and more expensive) bedroom, the so-called “Studio d’artiste”, with view on the Tour Eiffel. But in reality, even if you actually see the tour faraway, the main view is on a terribly noisy big road, with busses, horns, motor-bikes and everything you don’t want to look at and above all hear from your bed (windows are not enough sound proofed). It was so noisy that I asked for another bedroom, even a lower category, but an unfriendly employee said that they had no other possibility. When I mentioned that I could book another bedroom with my phone on Booking.com in front of his eyes, we said that it was not possible anyway for him to change my accommodation that day. He said also that managers were not available to discuss with. Luckly enough a more helpful colleague stepped in and gave me a smaller, no view bedroom, which was in principle calm, except for the very loud music in the afternoon from the hotel bar (they allow people from outside to have aperitif on the terrace, which is beautiful for breakfast but noisy and full of people in the afternoon). Positive thing: we got free breakfast (it is delicious) for the whole staying for free, in order to compensate the lower category.
However, I’m not sure I will go again to Terrass.

Having read reviews for this hotel on trip advisor we were expecting a good hotel and service at the very least but sadly we were very disappointed.
The positives first - great location and good sized rooms and excellent view from the roof top bar.
Now for the negatives - no hairdryer in the room despite being told there was one, we went through 4 remote controls for the tv during our 2 night stay ( we only wanted to catch up on the news), after the first day the room key failed to work so we had to go down to ask reception for a new one, the water in the shower was luke warm but never able to have a hot shower, we arrived back at our room at 4pm ( having left at 8am) to find that the room had not been cleaned yet - when we contacted reception they said it would be cleaned soon but because we wanted to rest we agreed that it would be cleaned at 7 pm but we had no teabags or milk as they had not been replenished so we had to go back down to reception yet again to pick these things up then on our arrival back at our room at 8.40pm the cleaner was still in the room and it was not yet ready, Reception were mildly apologetic but did not really appear to understand our frustrations. For the price we paid we would have expected much more than we got.
Would we go again? NO
Would we recommedn this hotel to anyone else? NO

Tho hotel is fabulous. Clean. Reception courteous. Excellent views from roof garden. Great location. Just up from Clichy. Next to Montmatre and place de tetre. Well worth a visit. Money well spent near moulin rouge. Great night there. The nightlife is superb. Would recommend this hotel

We stayed here for four nights in Feb 20 - it was our third time, it has undergone a major refurb/ refit but is still a very good base for a city break. The staff are knowledgable and friendly (good English as well). The breakfast is a high quality buffet in the seventh floor restaurant overlooking the Paris skyline and great views of the Eifel tower. There is also very popular seventh floor bar which gets quire busy with non- hotel guests enjoying thje view.
Loads of bar and restaurants within walking and the Metro is close enough.
Rooms are clean and decor good. We had a one on the first fllor which attracted a tad of traffic noise so maybe ask for a room on a higher floor.

We were greeted by a lovely friendly receiptionist who informed us that we had been upgraded to a room with a view of the Eiffel Tower.
We have visited Paris on manyt occasions and I can honestly say this was the best room we have ever had. It was clean and comfortable with everything you could want plust an amazing view over Paris and to the tower. We could even see the Tower from the shower as there was a window in it looking over the bed towards the doors to the balcony.

I highly recommend not only this hotel but this room in particular room 801.

The location is perfect with lots of bars and restautrants within easy walking distance and excellent access to the Metro in just a few minutes walk

Stayed here over the weekend with my Wife celebrating her Birthday, had a great time! Terrass is situated just a few minutes walk to some lovely shops & restaurants, very well decorated. We had a room on the top floor whilst was quite close to the restaurant & bar was not too loud & had great views! The staff especially on the front desk were lovely & very helpful - i would strongly recommend a stay here!!!

Very nicely decorated hotel conveniently located. Staff was very nice and checked us in right away. Room was comfy with a good sized bathroom. Rooftop restaurant was yummy and offered good assortment for breakfast.

I was very happy with the place n environment to seat n the quality of dishes is awesome. This is the first time I being ther n was tests of delicious starter is also more taste n very good set of table n spoons used.

Loved this hotel; veryfriendly staffsome bi-lingual too! Roomservice lovelyview of thecitygreat localmarket and goodlocal restaurants short distance fromhotel great area friendlybars and close metro station tour bus stop nearby rop restr with great viws ofcity

Great hotel in a perfect location. However breakfast @ 25 euros was a sorry affair, with only 2 hot options (scrambled eggs and tiny sausages) available.
That being said, the room was clean and a good size and the staff at reception were extremely helpful.
We would certainly visit again.
Graham Kingston.

We had a wonderful stay at Terrass Hotel. It's not in the busy part of the city, but it is near some attraction and only a 20min ride to the hustle and bustle of Paris. The hotel room was absolutely gorgeous. Very clean, modern design, and with wonderful amenities - the room was just like the photos, picture perfect. The room was very well designed, it had a convenient layout for the two of us and was so spacious. We stayed in the room with a view of the Eiffel Tower. When the fog rolled in it was harder to see, but when you could see it, it was exactly what you'd imagine. There are a few bakeries and cafes in an under 5min walk, which the locals would eat at, and plenty more further down. The room had a coffee machine with pods, tea, a Dyson blowdryer, and L'Occitane bath products. We had that luxury feel at an affordable price. A comfy bed with plenty of outlets around the room, a couch to lounge on, and a tablet in the room with a bunch of information about what is offered in the hotel and around the city. When leaving, we were able to easily arrange a taxi ride to the airport that is simply added to your tab. We visited the restaurant on the top floor but it was unfortunately closed at the time we went. On that same floor is a bar with nice seating and some games. If you are trying to get away from the city life and experience a neighborhood filled with more locals I would highly suggest Terrass. Renya (I hope I spelled that right) was helping us throughout our stay; she helped with check in, taxi, and check out - she was the perfect example of what hospitality should be! She was beyond helpful in providing suggestions of where to go and what to see, and always had a big smile. She made our experience at the hotel even more enjoyable.

Great neighborhood, staff was great. Everything I could’ve wanted. Stop looking just stay here. The location was perfect, close to metro and about 20 amazing restaurants. The bar at the top has a great view of the Eiffel Tower and a great selection of wine.

We had a wonderful two night stay at Terass. The rooms are clean, warm, comfortable and stylishly decorated.
The staff are extremely helpful, with the lady on reception recommending a great value restaurant on our first night. The rooftop bar has fantastic views of the Eiffell Tower and beyond. The hotel is also excellently located for those wanting to explore Montmartre, close to bars, cafes, shops and restaurants. There are also three Metro stops close by if you want to head into the centre of Paris. Highly recommended.

My partner and I have just come back from three nights at the terrass and it is amazing. We had room 507 which has a long balcony with a small table and chairs on. The view is incredible (Suite Artiste Eiffel) and the room itself is spacious with a sofa bed and seating area. The bed is really comfy (queen size) and the bathroom has got everything you need from loccitane products to a Dyson hairdryer. The breakfast is incredible in the restaurant. Overall could not fault this hotel. Great location, great rooms, great service. The hotel provided a travel cot and okay teepee for our daughter which she loved. We loved the room that much that we got engaged on the balcony at night whilst the tower was sparkling away in the background! Perfect.

Fantastic service by the super cute and handsome Enzo at the rooftop terrasse! We stayed for almost 4 hours, brunch was finished but we had snacks and wine!
You just have to try it! In Montmartre, close to Sacre Coeur.

We've just got back from a great weekend in Paris. We thoroughly enjoyed our stay at the Terrass. The service was excellent, room was fantastic and having a delicious breakfast every morning with a view of the Eiffel tower was just amazing. The hotel is in a fantastic area and position being so close to the Sacre Couer. Just 4 or 5 minutes walk away is the Place de Clichy metro station if you don't fancy walking into the centre.

What a Great Hotel. Brilliant service, very warm welcome. Amazing dinner with a spectacular view.....big room and clean. I will come again and we are looking forward to see you soon. You have to book room 604!!!

My better half and I spent a night at Terrass and wow! What an amazing view of the Eiffel Tower. The room were modern and sleek. Bright with lots of natural light.
There’s a restaurant on the roof with amazing views of Paris, including the Eiffel Tower. We had dinner so you can imagine how beautiful the city look with all the lights.

Superb views , ideal for access to Montmartre , Pigalle and central by a decent walk or metro . Excellent staff and clean spacious rooms , rooftop bar is gorgeous . Really can't fault this hotel at all.
